-- Microsoft to hold press call, not related to Yahoo
-- 
-- Thu Feb 21, 2008 9:17am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/21/us-microsoft-announcement-idUSWNAS186120080221

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Microsoft Corp ( MSFT.O ) said it will hold a press conference on Thursday for a "significant" company announcement, but the software maker said the news was not related to its $42 billion offer for Yahoo Inc ( YHOO.O ). 

 The company will hold a conference call at 11.30 a.m. EST with Chief Executive Steve Ballmer, chief software architect Ray Ozzie, senior vice president of server and tools Bob Muglia and general counsel Brad Smith. Further details were not disclosed. Microsoft shares rose 1.2 percent in premarket trading to $28.56 from its close of $28.22 on the Nasdaq on Wednesday. (Reporting by  Michele Gershberg , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)